ok sound. solid playing ok sound. solid playing. 
that said, there is NO TRANSITION between On the Road Again, and Touch of Grey. This sucks when people label the songs like this.I love a good song transition, and believe me...These are played seperately and do not merit a >.

Anybody miss out? When this show was uploaded it initially was available for download (not just streaming)...I just grabbed it immediately and didn't think twice.  If anyone needs it, e-mail me at:
craigeyler@yahoo.com

Very well-played show, and excellent sound for a late '82 board.  '82 is pretty spotty in general sound-wise, although the July/August shows are for the most part spot-on.  The sound quality on this one rates about a 3.5 or a 4.0, definitely higher quality than other boards from this run I've come across, and a cut above the previously available board of THIS show.  Probably shouldn't say CUT, let's say a notch above.  On The Road Again in 1982 was fun, what the hell.  Plus a Shakedown and Terrapin and a lot of well-played first set songs too.  Go for this one!

speed check a tiny tiny bit too fast?

compare to the other version of this nite, see if you agree.

It is a small, but audible difference.

Mein lieblingShakedown!!!--Loose Coast Style! The other show was here last week!!??  What happened?  This is one of my all-time favorite Shakedowns. Obviously Jerry is literally just poking around for some lyrics-(it justs adds to the dark aura of this song IMO) but the music is STELLAR!! It just smokes--and just feels edgy and high. Just a funky, long winded meltdown of a jam--then we abruptly fumble into Samson (thanks for the giggles Mr. Weir!!) and the rest of a juicy set.....Hot show  in the opinion of these ears-nice. Holiday treat @ the time, I am sure for all those involved.

Shakedown in total agreement Burnt Rich's review nailed it.  This Shakedown is funny right from the start.  The opening line is just mutilated and doesn't let up on the rest of the lyrics either.  Makes you realize, who cares?  It's the music that we choose.  Maybe Jer had too much too fast that night?
